folder: Ryder Avenue & Avenue S, Brooklyn, NY
text:
(1) Ryder ave., at the S.W. corner of Ave. S., showing the home of E. Ryder (1857) and E.H. Ryder (1860-1873). It was occupied by one Hill in 1922. This house, in the Brooklyn Atlas of 1929, is in East 29th Street, just south of Ave. S., and will either be moved or demolished at a subsequent date.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same, looking north on Ryder Ave.

April 1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3) The same, showing the barns near East 28th Street.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(4) The same, viewed from Ave. S.

April 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
